edu.brown.cs.gk16.stars

Class StarsObject

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.brown.cs.gk16.stars.StarsObject

  • public class StarsObject
extends Object
    This class is the representation of a collection of stars existing in a kdtree that can be queried 1) to find the nearest k neighbors given a star or point and 2) to find all the stars in a radius around a given star or point. Both algorithms are housed in this class - as well as the csv reading related to uploading the stars.

      • nearestNeighbor

        public List<String> nearestNeighbor(int neighbors,
                                    List<Double> point)
        Searches for the nearest k (delineated by the integer neighbors) neighbors in the kd tree to the point given by point and returns them in a sorted list of their ids as strings (in order of nearest to furthest). Uses the function searchSubTree as a recursive helper that recurses down each subtree. Returns an empty list if the number of neighbors specified is 0 or if the point given is null
        Parameters:
        neighbors - the number of neighbors to search for
        point - a point whose neighbors to search for
        Returns:
        a sorted list of the nearest k neighbors

      • rangeSearch

        public List<String> rangeSearch(double radius,
                                List<Double> point)
        Searches for all the stars in the kd tree that are within the range of radius from the given point. Then returns them in a sorted list of their ids as strings (in order of nearest to furthest). Uses the function searchRangeSubTree as a recursive helper that recurses down each subtree. Returns an empty list if the radius specified is 0 or if the point given is null
        Parameters:
        radius - radial distance within which to find stars
        point - the point around which the radius is centered
        Returns:
        a sorted list of the stars within range
